e not released in that region.}}\n|}\n\n==Filmography==\n=== Television shows ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! English title\n! Original title\n! Network\n! Notes\n! Ref.\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2018 || ''[[Real Man 300]]'' || \uc9c4\uc9dc\uc0ac\ub098\uc774 300 || [[MBC TV|MBC]] || Cast member || <ref>{{Cite news|author=Woo Bin|title='\uc9c4\uc9dc\uc0ac\ub098\uc774300' 2\ucc28 \ub77c\uc778\uc5c5 \uacf5\uac1c, NCT \ub8e8\uce74\uc2a4X\ubaac\uc2a4\ud0c0\uc5d1\uc2a4 \uc154\ub204 '\uccb4\ub825\u738b' \uc778\uc99d|url=http://tenasia.hankyung.com/archives/1560378|website=TenAsia|date=September 3, 2018|accessdate=March 17, 2019|language=ko}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[List of Law of the Jungle episodes #Indian Ocean 2|Law of the Jungle in Last Indian Ocean]]'' || \uc815\uae00\uc758 \ubc95\uce59 || [[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]] || Cast member || <ref>{{Cite news|author=Hwang Ji-young|title=[\ub2e8\ub3c5] \uc815\uc138\uc6b4\u00b7\uae40\ub3c4\uc5f0\u00b7\ub8e8\uce74\uc2a4\u00b7\uc5f0\uc6b0, '\uc815\uae00\uc758 \ubc95\uce59' \ud569\ub958|url=http://news.jtbc.joins.com/article/article.aspx?news_id=NB11667173|work=[[JTBC]] News|date=July 18, 2018|accessdate=March 17, 2019|language=ko}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2019 || ''[[Keep Running (TV series)|Keep Running]]'' || \u5954\u8dd1\u5427 ||[[Zhejiang Television|ZRTG]]|| Cast member || <ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.zaobao.com.sg/zentertainment/movies-and-tv/story20190212-931267|title=\u300a\u5954\u8dd1\u5427\u300b\u6210\u5458\u5927\u6362\u8840 \u738b\u7956\u84dd\u9093\u8d85\u9e7f\u6657\u79bb\u961f|work=Zaobao|publisher=|language=zh|date=February 12, 2019|accessdate=March 11, 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist-ua}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n* [https://m.weibo.cn/u/6989405838 Lucas Wong] on [[Sina Weibo]]\n* [https://www.instagram.com/lucas_xx444/ Lucas Wong] on [[Instagram]]\n\n{{NCT (band)}}\n{{SM Entertainment}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lucas Wong}}\n[[Category:1999 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Hong Kong male rappers]]\n[[Category:Hong Kong male models]]\n[[Category:Hong Kong male singers]]\n[[Category:Chinese K-pop singers]]\n[[Category:SuperM members]]\n[[Category:Korean-language singers of Hong Kong]]\n[[Category:Chinese television personalities]]\n[[Category:21st-century male singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Chinese singers]]\n[[Category:Hong Kong expatriates in South Korea]]\n[[Category:Hong Kong people of Thai descent]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Hong Kong singer}}\n{{Use Hong Kong English|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Chinese name|[[Huang (surname)|Wong]]}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Lucas Wong\n| image              = Lucas Wong at 24th Dream Concert 02.png\n| image_size         = \n| landscape          = \n| caption            = Wong at 24th Dream Concert in 2018\n| native_name        = \u9ec3\u65ed\u7199\n| native_name_lang   = zh\n| alias              = \n| birth_name         = Wong Yuk-hei\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1999|1|25}}\n| birth_place        = [[Sha Tin]], Hong Kong\n| nationality        = Hong Kong\n| alma_mater         = TWGHs Yow Kam Yuen College\n| occupation         = {{hlist|Rapper|singer|model|dancer}}\n| signature          = \n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| background       = solo_singer<!--mandatory field-->\n| genre            = {{hlist|[[C-pop]]|[[K-pop]]|[[Cantopop]]}}\n| instrument       = Vocal\n| years_active     = 2018\u2013present\n| label            = {{hlist|[[SM Entertainment|SM]]|[[Label V]]|[[Capitol Records|Capitol]]}}\n| associated_acts  = {{hlist|[[NCT (group)|NCT]]|NCT U|[[WayV]]|[[SuperM]]|[[SM Rookies]]|[[SM Town]]}}\n}}\n| module2            = {{Chinese\n | child = yes\n | t = {{linktext|\u9ec3|\u65ed|\u7199}}\n | s = {{linktext|\u9ec4|\u65ed|\u7199}}\n | p = Hu\u00e1ng X\u00f9x\u012b\n | w = Huang Hsu-hsi\n | j = Wong Juk Hei\n |\n}}\n{{ Infobox Korean name | child = yes\n | hangul = {{linktext|\ud669|\uc6b1|\ud76c}}\n | hanja = {{linktext|\u9ec3|\u65ed|\u7199}}\n | rr = Hwang Uk-hui\n | mr = Hwang Uk-h\u016di\n | hangulstage = {{lang|ko|{{linktext|\ub8e8|\uce74|\uc2a4|}}}}\n | rrstage = Lukaseu\n | mrstage = Ruk'as\u016d\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Wong Yuk-hei''' ({{zh|c=|first=t|t={{linktext|\u9ec3|\u65ed|\u7199}}|s={{linktext|\u9ec4|\u65ed|\u7199}}}}, born 25 January 1999), better known by the [[Mononymous person|mononym]] '''Lucas''', is a [[Hong Kong people|Hong Kong]] rapper, singer, and model. He is a member of the South Korean [[boy group]] [[NCT (group)|NCT]] and its sub-units [[NCT (group)|NCT U]] and [[WayV]], as well as [[SM Entertainment]] [[Supergroup (music)|supergroup]], [[SuperM]].\n\n==Early life==\nLucas was born on 25 January 1999 in [[Sha Tin]], Hong Kong, to a [[Chinese people|Chinese]] father and a [[Thai people|Thai]] mother.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EMhxUKtqD9k |title=\ub2e4\uad6d\uc5b4\uc655 \ub8e8\uce74\uc2a4(Lucas), \uc5b4\uc124\ud508 \ud0dc\uad6d\uc5b4\uc5d0 \ubc40\ubc40(Bam Bam) \"\uc798 \ubabb\ud558\ub294\ub370?\" \uc544\ub294 \ud615\ub2d8(Knowing bros) 141\ud68c|language=ko}}</ref> He has one younger brother and attended [[Tung Wah Group of Hospitals]] Yow Kam Yuen College.<ref>{{cite news|language=zh-hk |author=\u9673\u8a60\u598d |url=https://www.hk01.com/\u97d3\u8ff7/82790/sm\u5a1b\u6a02\u9996\u4f4d\u9999\u6e2f\u85dd\u4ebalucas\u9ec3\u65ed\u7199-\u6700\u611bexid-hani\u91d1\u6240\u70ab\u6975\u6709\u7570\u6027\u7de3 |title=SM\u5a1b\u6a02\u9996\u4f4d\u9999\u6e2f\u85dd\u4ebaLucas\u9ec3\u65ed\u7199 |publisher=[[HK01]] |date=6 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n===2015-2017: Pre-Debut===\nIn 2015, Lucas was scouted by [[SM Entertainment]], a South Korean entertainment agency, after passing a Global Audition that was held in Hong Kong. Lucas was accepted after only one modeling audition.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.soompi.com/article/1216981wpp/ncts-lucas-reveals-passed-sm-entertainment-auditions-ease|title=NCT\u2019s Lucas Reveals How He Passed SM Entertainment Auditions With Ease|date=1534604589|website=Soompi|language=en|access-date=2019-11-06}}</ref> As an SM trainee, Lucas received training in singing, rapping, and dancing.  On April 5, 2017, he was introduced as a member of [[SM Rookies]], a Pre-Debut Training Team composed of young trainees who would potentially debut as idol group members. On April 7, 2017, Lucas made a cameo appearance in NCT member Ten's \"Dream In A Dream\" music video. Lucas, whose mother tongue is [[Cantonese]], studied [[Korean language|Korean]] and [[Standard Chinese|Mandarin]] in preparation for his debut.\n\n===2018\u2013present: Debut with NCT, WayV and solo activities===\nIn January 2018, SM Entertainment unveiled NCT 2018, a project group for the expansive boy group [[NCT (group)|NCT]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.xportsnews.com/jenter/?ac=article_view&entry_id=933151&_REFERER=https%3A%2F%2Fsearch.daum.net%2Fsearch%3Fw%3Dnews%26nil_search%3Dbtn%26DA%3DNTB%26enc%3Dutf8%26cluster%3Dy%26cluster_page%3D1%26q%3DNCT|title=[\ub2e8\ub3c5] NCT, \u65b0 \ub300\ud615 \ud504\ub85c\uc81d\ud2b8 \ucef4\ubc31 \uc2dc\ub3d9\u2026\uc2e0\uace1 \ubba4\ube44\uc704\ud574 \ucd9c\uad6d|date=January 15, 2018|website=Xports News|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/8257671/nct-explained-empathy-album-world-digital-song-sales-chart-127-dream-u|title=Three NCT Teams Debut on World Digital Song Sales Chart: Your Guide to Each One|work=Billboard|date=March 23, 2018}}</ref> Lucas, together with Kun and Jungwoo, were the group's newest members. The trio were introduced in SM's ''NCT 2018 Yearbook #1'' on 30 January 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.sbs.co.kr/news/endPage.do?news_id=N1004599958&plink=SEARCH&cooper=SBSNEWSSEARCH|title=NCT Unveils 3 New Members; JUNGWOO, KUN and LUCAS!|date=January 31, 2018|website=SBS News}}</ref> Lucas officially made his debut with NCT on March 14, with their debut [[studio album]] ''[[NCT 2018 Empathy]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20180315000244|title=Global boy band project NCT on attack as full group|date=March 15, 2018|website=The Korea Herald}}</ref> Lucas recorded three songs in the album as part of the sub-unit NCT U, including title tracks \"Boss,\" \"Yestoday\" (both as NCT U), and \"Black on Black\" (as NCT 2018).<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/8205906/nct-u-boss-video|title=NCT U Shows the World Who Is 'Boss' in Charismatic New Video|work=Billboard|date=February 19, 2018|accessdate=March 22, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/8280656/nct-u-yestoday-new-music-video-watch-k-pop-sm-entertainment|title=NCT U Say 'Yestoday' in New Music Video: Watch|date=April 2, 2018|website=Billboard|accessdate=March 22, 2019}}</ref> To promote the album, Lucas appeared on Korean variety shows ''[[Real Man 300]]'' and ''[[List of Law of the Jungle episodes #Indian Ocean 2|Law of the Jungle in Last Indian Ocean]]'' as regular cast members.\n\nLucas was featured on [[Kim Tae-yeon|Taeyeon]]'s song \"All Night Long,\" a track recorded in her [[extended play|EP]] ''[[Something New (EP)|Something New]]'', released in June 2018. The song peaked at number 72 on the [[Gaon Digital Chart]]. In November 2018, Lucas released the digital single \"Coffee Break,\" with [[Dirty Loops|Jonah Nilsson]] and featuring Richard Bona, for ''[[SM Station discography|SM Station 3]]''. \n\nIn December 2018, Lucas was announced to be a part of NCT's China-based unit [[WayV]], managed by Label V. The seven-member unit officially debuted on January 17, 2019 with their debut [[Extended play|EP]] ''[[The Vision (WayV EP)|The Vision]]''. Its lead single \"Regular\" was the Mandarin remake of \"[[Regular-Irregular|Regular]]\" by [[NCT 127]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.weibo.cn/profile/6903448926|title=WayV_official|website=Weibo|language=zh}}</ref><ref name=\"entertain.naver.com\">{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/now/read?oid=109&aid=0003929238|title=SM \"\u4e2d\uc2e0\uc778 \uc6e8\uc774\uc158\ube0c\uc774, 2019\ub144 1\uc6d4 \ub370\ubdd4\ud655\uc815\"\u2026NCT \ub300\uac70 \ud569\ub958 [\uacf5\uc2dd\uc785\uc7a5]|date=December 31, 2018|website=Osen|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/tamarherman/2019/01/16/wayv-represents-sm-entertainments-goals-for-global-dominance-through-cultural-technology/|title=WayV Represents SM Entertainment's Goals For Global Dominance Through Cultural Technology |last=Herman |first=Tamar |website=Forbes |access-date=2019-01-20}}</ref> The following month, Lucas joined the cast of Chinese variety show ''[[Keep Running (TV series)|Keep Running]]'' as a fixed cast member for the [[Keep Running (season 7)|seventh season]]. \n\nOn August 7, 2019, Lucas was announced as a member of [[SuperM]], a K-pop \"supergroup\" created by SM Entertainment in collaboration with [[Capitol Records]]. The group's promotions began in October and are aimed at the American market.<ref>{{cite news |author1=Jeff Benjamin |title=Super M, 'The Avengers Of K-Pop,' Unveiled By SM Entertainment And Capitol Music Group |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jeffbenjamin/2019/08/07/super-m-the-avengers-of-k-pop-unveiled-by-sm-entertainment-and-capitol-music-group/#355dfa061381 |accessdate=1 September 2019 |publisher=Forbes |date=7 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=SM Entertainment and Capitol Records Team Up to Launch Super M |url=https://www.billboard.com/video/bbnews080819tiffanykpop2-8526949 |accessdate=1 September 2019 |publisher=Billboard |date=8 August 2019}}</ref> SuperM's [[SuperM (EP)|self-titled debut EP]] was released on October 4, 2019 with lead single \"Jopping\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8532879/superm-the-1st-mini-album-billboard-200-no-1|title=SuperM Debuts at No. 1 on Billboard 200 Albums Chart With 'The 1st Mini Album'|website=Billboard|access-date=2020-02-17}}</ref> On October 5, Lucas has his first concert with SuperM at the [[Capitol Records Building]] in [[Los Angeles]], preceding a world tour with stops in North America and planned stops in Europe and Asia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20191002000672|title=Q&A: SuperM answers big questions before its debut this week|last=Herald|first=The Korea|date=2019-10-02|website=www.koreaherald.com|language=en|access-date=2020-02-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.getsurrey.co.uk/whats-on/music-nightlife-news/superm-announce-london-o2-arena-17465086|title=SuperM announce London O2 Arena show on world tour|last=Yates|first=Jonathan|date=2019-12-23|website=getwestlondon|access-date=2020-02-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/superm_jp/status/1227880739464630272|title=2020\u5e744\u670823\u65e5(\u6728) \u2019SuperM We Are The Future Live\u2019\u306e\u6771\u4eac\u30c9\u30fc\u30e0\u516c\u6f14\u304c\u6c7a\u5b9a\u3057\u307e\u3057\u305f\uff01|last=SuperM_JP|first=|date=2020-02-13|website=www.twitter.com|language=ja|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-17}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n{{See also|NCT discography|WayV #Discography|SuperM#Discography}}\n\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"3\" scope=\"col\" style=\"width:18em;\" | Title\n! rowspan=\"3\" scope=\"col\" | Year\n! Peak chart positions\n! rowspan=\"3\" scope=\"col\" style=\"width:12em;\" | Album\n|-\n! KOR\n|-\n!style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Gaon Digital Chart|Gaon]]<br><ref>Peak positions for songs on the Gaon Digital Chart:\n* {{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=ALL&targetTime=25&hitYear=2018&termGbn=week |title=All Night Long\"|date=June 28, 2018}}\n</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Coffee Break\"<br>{{small|(with [[Dirty Loops]] featuring [[Richard Bona]])}}\n| 2018\n| \u2014\n| ''[[SM Station discography#2018\u20132019: Season 3|SM Station: Season 3]]''\n|-\n| colspan=\"8\" |{{small|\"\u2014\" denotes songs that did not chart or were not released in that region.}}\n|}\n\n===Soundtrack appearances===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"3\" scope=\"col\" style=\"width:12em;\" | Title\n! rowspan=\"3\" scope=\"col\" | Year\n! colspan=\"3\" |Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"3\" | Sales\n! rowspan=\"3\" scope=\"col\" | Album\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\"| CHN\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:4em;font-size:90%\" |[[Gaon Music Chart|KOR]]\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Billboard China Top 100|CHN]]<br><ref name=\"top100\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboardchina.cn/top/top100/|title=Billboard China Top 100|website=Billboard China|accessdate=June 12, 2019|language=zh}}\n</ref>{{efn|group=upper-alpha|The [[Billboard China Top 100]] was launched in January 2019 by [[Billboard China]].}}\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\" |[[QQ Music|QQ]]<br><ref>Charted songs on [[QQ Music]]:</ref>\n|-\n! colspan=\"7\" | Collaborations\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"\u9020\u4ebf\u4e07\u5428\u5149\u8292\"<br>{{small|(with [[Angelababy]], [[Li Chen (actor)|Li Chen]], [[Zheng Kai]], [[Zhu Yawen]], [[Wang Yanlin]], [[Song Yuqi]])}}\n| 2019\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| {{N/A}}\n| ''[[Keep Running (TV series)|Keep Running]]'' theme song\n|-\n| colspan=\"7\" |{{small|\"\u2014\" denotes releases that did not chart or were not released in that region.}}\n|}\n\n===Other charted songs===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"3\" scope=\"col\" style=\"width:14em;\" | Title\n! rowspan=\"3\" scope=\"col\" | Year\n! Peak chart positions\n! rowspan=\"3\" scope=\"col\" | Album\n|-\n! KOR\n|-\n!style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Gaon Digital Chart|Gaon]]<br><ref>Peak positions for songs on the Gaon Digital 